extendedInfo.detail: Breaded white meat chicken patties, macaroni & cheese sauce, and sweet corn.  Per 1 Meal: 440 calories; 3.5 g sat fat (18% DV); 1070 mg sodium (47% DV); 9 g total sugars.  Since 1953. Banquet invites you to pull up a chair and enjoy classic, made-in-America comfort food. Like you, we believe in quality and good, honest value and trust you'll taste it in our delicious chicken strips that are served with a helping of creamy macaroni and cheese and sweet corn. SmartLabel: Scan or call 1-800-257-5191 for more food information.  Questions or comments, visit us at www.banquet.com or call 1-800-257-5191.
extendedInfo.ingredients: Breaded Chicken Strip Patties: Breaded Chicken Breast Patties With Rib Meat (Water, Chicken Breast With Rib Meat, Bread Crumbs [Bleached Wheat Flour, Salt, Dextrose, Yeast, Spice, Extractives Of Paprika], Textured Soy Flour, Batter Mix [Yellow Corn Flour, Corn Starch, Salt, Spices, Guar Gum, Leavening {Sodium Acid Pyrophosphate, Sodium Bicarbonate, Monocalcium Phosphate}, Garlic Powder], Less Than 2% Of: Modified Corn Starch, Salt, Autolyzed Yeast Extract, Sodium Phosphates, Flavorings, Fried In Vegetable Oil). Macaroni And Cheese Sauce: Sauce (Water, Cheddar Club Cheese [Pasteurized Cultured Milk, Salt, Enzymes, Annatto {Color}], Modified Whey, Soybean Oil, Modified Corn Starch, Nonfat Dry Milk, Salt, Cheddar Cheese Flavor [Cheddar Cheese {Pasteurized Milk, Cultures, Salt, Enzymes}, Water, Lactic Acid, Yeast Extract, Salt, Disodium Phosphate, Sodium Citrate, Xanthan Gum], Sugar, Sodium Phosphates, Xanthan Gum, Citric Acid, Guar Gum, Sunflower Oil, Beta Carotene [Color]), Cooked Enriched Macaroni (Water, Enriched Macaroni Product [Durum Wheat Semolina, Niacin, Iron {Ferrous Sulfate}, Thiamin Mononitrate, Riboflavin, Folic Acid]). Corn: Corn, Water, Sugar, Salt.
extendedInfo.directions: Microwave Oven: Cook only one at a time. Remove film from meal; remove chicken strips. Microwave on High 1 minute. Stir macaroni & cheese and replace chicken strips. Microwave an additional 3 to 3 minutes. Check that food is cooked thoroughly to 165 degrees F. Careful, it's hot! Let stand 2 minutes; stir macaroni & cheese and enjoy! Conventional Oven: Do not prepare in toaster oven. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Remove film over chicken strips. Cook on baking sheet in center of oven 26 to 28 minutes. Check that food is cooked thoroughly to 165 degrees F. Careful it's hot! Let stand 2 minutes; stir macaroni & cheese and enjoy! Must be cooked thoroughly. For Food Safety and Quality: Keep frozen. Do not thaw. Appliances vary. Adjust cooking times as needed. Microwave directions developed with 1100-watt microwave ovens. Food must be cooked thoroughly to 165 degrees F. Read and follow these cooking directions.  Keep frozen.
